initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: Olly Alexander: "I'm feeling really excited and a bit nervous, to be honest. It's a huge platform and I want to make sure I give it my all. I've been rehearsing non-stop, perfecting my performance and making sure I'm in top vocal shape. I've also been working on my stage presence, trying to connect with the audience and bring the energy of the song to life. It's going to be a wild ride!"

"I've been thinking about the setlist nonstop, trying to curate the perfect mix of old and new songs to get the crowd moving. I've also been working on some new choreography, trying to push the boundaries of what's possible on stage. I've always been a fan of the theatricality of performance, so I'm excited to bring that to the show. And of course, I'm a bit worried about the pressure of performing in front of such a huge audience, but I'm trying to focus on the excitement of sharing my music with so many people."

"I've been rehearsing nonstop, perfecting every note and movement, and I'm starting to feel a sense of confidence building. I've also been thinking about the visuals and lighting, wanting to create an immersive experience that complements the music. I've been inspired by some of my favorite shows and artists, and I'm excited to put my own spin on things. But despite all the preparation, I know that anything can happen on the night of the show, and I'm trying to stay present and adaptable. I just want to give the audience an unforgettable night, and I'm hoping that all my hard work will pay off."

"As I stand backstage, waiting for the lights to go down, I can feel my heart racing with anticipation. I take a deep breath, trying to calm my nerves, and remind myself of all the hours I've put in. I think about the crowd, imagining their faces and reactions, and I feel a surge of adrenaline. The music starts, and I'm off, lost in the performance. It's like a dream, everything falling into place, and I'm completely in the zone. The lights, the music, the movement – it all comes together in a way that's even more magical than I imagined. And when it's all over, and the crowd erupts into applause, I feel an overwhelming sense of pride and accomplishment. It was everything I hoped for and more."

"As I take my final bow, I'm met with a sea of smiling faces and waving arms, and I feel like I'm on top of the world. The rush of adrenaline still coursing through my veins, I make my way offstage, already thinking about the next performance, the next challenge, the next opportunity to push myself to new heights. The thrill of the show is still coursing through my veins as I meet my fellow performers, exchanging stories and laughter, reliving the magic of the night. And as I make my way back to my dressing room, I know that this is what it's all about – the rush of the performance, the thrill of the applause, the sense of accomplishment and pride that comes with giving it your all."

"As I change out of my costume and begin to unwind, I can't help but think about the journey that brought me to this moment. The long hours of rehearsal, the setbacks and disappointments, the moments of doubt and uncertainty. But it was all worth it, I think, as I look around at the mementos and reminders of past performances that line my dressing room walls. The faded programs, the worn-out shoes, the tattered costume pieces – they all tell a story of perseverance and dedication, of a passion that refuses to be extinguished. And as I take a deep breath, feeling the weight of the evening slowly lifting from my shoulders, I know that I'm ready to do it all again, to take on the next challenge, to push myself to new heights and see where it takes me."

"The thought sends a thrill through me, a sense of excitement and anticipation that I've been craving all day. I think about the next show, the next role, the next challenge, and my mind starts racing with possibilities. I imagine the rush of adrenaline as I take the stage, the roar of the crowd, the thrill of bringing a character to life. And as I begin to pack up my things, I feel a sense of gratitude wash over me, gratitude for this life, for this craft, for the opportunity to do what I love. I take one last look around my dressing room, committing every detail to memory, and then I'm out the door, ready to take on whatever comes next."

"As I step out into the cool evening air, I'm greeted by the familiar sight of the city lights twinkling like diamonds against the dark sky. I take a deep breath, feeling the stress and tension of the day melt away, replaced by a sense of freedom and possibility. I hail a taxi and give the driver the address of my favorite coffee shop, where I know I'll find a quiet corner and a warm cup of coffee waiting for me. As we glide through the traffic, I pull out my phone and scroll through the messages from my friends and family, feeling grateful for their love and support. And when we finally arrive at the coffee shop, I take a seat at my usual table by the window, feeling a sense of contentment wash over me as I settle in for a well-deserved break."

"The aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the air, and I take a moment to appreciate the simple pleasures in life. I order a latte and a slice of lemon pound cake, and as I wait for my treats to arrive, I pull out my journal and begin to write, letting my thoughts and feelings flow onto the page. The sounds of the coffee shop fade into the background as I become lost in my own little world, reflecting on the past week and all its ups and downs. The words start to flow, and before I know it, I've filled several pages with my thoughts and musings. As I finish writing, I take a sip of my latte and feel a sense of clarity and peace wash over me, knowing that I've taken a moment to prioritize my own well-being and recharge for the days ahead."

"As I sit back in my chair, feeling refreshed and rejuvenated, I notice a woman sitting across from me, typing away on her laptop. She looks up and catches my eye, and I smile, feeling a sense of connection to this stranger. We strike up a conversation, bonding over our shared love of coffee and writing, and before I know it, we've been chatting for over an hour. The coffee shop is starting to close, and we reluctantly say our goodbyes, exchanging numbers and making plans to meet up again soon. As I leave the shop, I feel grateful for the unexpected encounter and the sense of community that it brought me."

"I walk out into the crisp evening air, feeling invigorated and inspired by the chance meeting. I take a deep breath, savoring the scent of freshly brewed coffee and the sound of distant chatter, and make my way home. As I walk, I can't help but think about the woman, whose name is Sophia, and the way our conversation flowed effortlessly. I find myself wondering what she's working on, what her passions are, and what kind of stories she's writing. I pull out my phone and send her a text, asking her to meet up for brunch the following weekend. The response comes quickly, and we make plans to meet at a trendy new spot in town. I spend the rest of the evening lost in thought, replaying our conversation and imagining all the possibilities that this new friendship might bring."

"As I drift off to sleep, I'm still replaying the highlights of our conversation, and I find myself smiling at the memory of Sophia's infectious laugh and the way her eyes sparkled when she talked about her writing. I wake up the next morning feeling refreshed and excited, and I spend the morning researching the trendy new spot where we're meeting for brunch. I arrive early, and as I take a seat at the table, I notice Sophia walking in, looking even more radiant than I remembered. We hug warmly, and as we sit down to order, I ask her about her writing, and she tells me about the novel she's working on, a sweeping historical romance that's been years in the making. I'm captivated by her passion and dedication, and as we dig into our food, I find myself feeling grateful for this chance encounter that's brought us together."

"As we linger over our coffee, Sophia asks me about my own creative pursuits, and I find myself opening up about my long-abandoned dream of writing a screenplay. She listens intently, her eyes lighting up with encouragement, and before I know it, we're making plans to meet up again soon to work on our respective projects together. The afternoon sun casts a warm glow over the bustling café, and as we part ways, I feel a sense of excitement and possibility that I haven't felt in a long time. I spend the rest of the day lost in thought, replaying our conversation and wondering what other adventures this new connection might bring."

"I find myself scrolling through my old notes and scripts, dusting off the cobwebs of forgotten ideas. Sophia's enthusiasm has reignited a spark within me, and I'm eager to dive back into the world of storytelling. As I settle into my favorite armchair, surrounded by the familiar comforts of my home, I feel a sense of calm wash over me. The hours slip away, and I'm lost in the thrill of creation, the world outside fading into the background as I lose myself in the story."

"The words spill out of me like a dam breaking, the characters' voices whispering in my ear as I scribble furiously to keep up with their tales. The room around me dissolves, and I'm transported to the world I'm creating, the sights, sounds, and smells vividly alive. "The thread, however, is tangled and knotty, a mess of ideas and emotions that refuse to be untangled.
